ciscoLecDataVccMIB.name: ciscoLecDataVccMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoLecDataVccMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-atm@cisco.com
ciscoLecDataVccMIB.description: This MIB module is a Cisco extension to the ATM Forum's LANE Client MIB. This extension identifies those VCCs which are being used to carry packets sent on LANE Data Direct VCCs.

cLecDataDirectVccTable.name: cLecDataDirectVccTable
cLecDataDirectVccTable.description: A table containing entries for all VCCs used as LAN-Emulation Data Direct VCCs.

cLecDataDirectVccEntry.name: cLecDataDirectVccEntry
cLecDataDirectVccEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a Data Direct VCC for a particular Emulated LAN (ELAN): - the ELAN is identified by the lecIndex value. - the VCC is identified by the combination of the interface (ifIndex, for which the corresponding ifType has the value atm(37)), the VPI (atmVclVpi) and the VCI (atmVclVci). Entries appear in the table as a LANE client establishes Data Direct VCs with other LANE clients and are removed when the VCs are dropped.

cLecDataDirectLocalAtmAddress.name: cLecDataDirectLocalAtmAddress
cLecDataDirectLocalAtmAddress.description: The ATM Address of the local end of this Data Direct VCC.

cLecDataDirectRemoteAtmAddress.name: cLecDataDirectRemoteAtmAddress
cLecDataDirectRemoteAtmAddress.description: The ATM Address of the remote end of this Data Direct VCC.

ciscoLecDataVccMIBCompliance.name: ciscoLecDataVccMIBCompliance
ciscoLecDataVccMIBCompliance.description: This module should be implemented by all Cisco devices supporting ATM LAN Emulation Clients.

ciscoLecDataVccBaseMIBGroup.name: ciscoLecDataVccBaseMIBGroup
ciscoLecDataVccBaseMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects related to identifying a LANE Client's Data Direct VCCs.
